SIMPLE: tapetum
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tapetum
<hw>Ta*pe"tum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from L.
<ets>tapete</ets> a carpet, a tapestry.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>An area in the pigmented layer of the choroid coat of the eye in
many animals, which has an iridescent or metallic luster and helps to
make the eye visible in the dark. Sometimes applied to the whole layer
of pigmented epithelium of the choroid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tapeworm</ent>⟦br⟧
